"Emergency medical responder" means an individual who has:
Completed an emergency medical responder course approved by the EMS Board, or its equivalent as determined by the EMS Board;
Demonstrated competence in medical protocols as determined by the EMS Board;
Been examined by the EMS Board or by a basic life support education program approved by the EMS Board; and
Been certified as an emergency medical responder by the EMS Board.

"Emergency medical services" means:
Medical services provided prehospital to prevent imminent death or aggravation of illness or injury whether or not transport to a hospital or appropriate facility occurs;
Transport from the scene of a medical emergency to a hospital or appropriate facility whether or not medical services are provided;
Medical interfacility transport services to an appropriate facility; or
Medical interfacility critical care transport to an appropriate facility.

"Emergency medical services provider" means an individual licensed or certified by the EMS Board as:
A cardiac rescue technician;
An emergency medical dispatcher;
An emergency medical responder;
An emergency medical technician; or
A paramedic.

"Paramedic" means an individual who has:
Completed a paramedic course approved by the EMS Board;
Been examined and registered by the National Registry of Emergency Medical Technicians, Inc. as a paramedic;
Demonstrated competence in medical protocols within this State as determined by the EMS Board; and
Been licensed as a paramedic by the EMS Board.

This section does not apply to:
An individual who:
Has completed an emergency medical services course or its equivalent as determined by the EMS Board;
Is authorized to provide emergency medical services by any state adjoining this State;
Is called on by a public safety agency providing emergency medical services to render emergency medical services in this State or to transport emergency patients from the adjoining state to a health care facility in this State;
Is providing emergency medical services within the scope of the license or certificate issued to the individual by the other state; and
Is not affiliated with an emergency medical service in this State or is not engaged in providing emergency medical services in this State on a regular basis;
An individual who is enrolled in an emergency medical services provider training program that meets the standards set by the EMS Board in the course of that training;
An individual who is not engaged in providing emergency medical services on a regular basis who provides emergency medical services at the scene of a medical emergency in rare instances;
An individual who is a member of a volunteer fire or rescue company and solely engaged in driving the emergency vehicle;
An individual who assists an emergency medical services provider but does not directly provide emergency medical services;
An individual who has American Red Cross first aid training or its equivalent and who provides services within the scope of that training, does not respond to emergency calls, and does not transport patients; or
A law enforcement officer who:
Has successfully completed a course:
Provides services within the scope of that training; and
Is not dispatched as an emergency medical services provider.

Subject to the hearing provisions of subsection (i) of this section and as a result of any conduct of an emergency medical services provider or an applicant for a license or certificate under this section that is prohibited under the provisions of this section or any regulations adopted under this section, the EMS Board may:
Reprimand or place an emergency medical services provider on probation;
Suspend or revoke the license or certificate of an emergency medical services provider;
Deny a license or certificate to an applicant; or
Refuse to renew an applicant's license or certificate.
